                                    <list>
                                        <item>
                                            <p>Vellum, about 10 1/4 in. by 6 3/4, consisting of 23
                                                leaves, some of which are much stained and torn,
                                                especially foil. 1, 4—6, 12—15, 17—21, and 23. The
                                                quires are signed with letters, and were originally
                                                at least 22 in number (fol 7 a, ܛ; fol. 21 a, ܟܒ);
                                                but not a single one is now perfect. As at present
                                                bound, there are lacunae after foll. 4, 5, 6, 7, 8,
                                                10, 12, 13, 14, 15, 16, 18, and 22. Each page is
                                                divided into two columns, of from 34 to 38 lines.
                                                This volume is written in a good, current hand of
                                                the vith or viith cent. </p>
                                        </item>
                                    </list>
                                </condition>
