                        <additions>
                            <p></p>
                            <list>
                                <item>
                                    <locus from="23" to=""/>
                                    <p>Whether the fly-leaf, fol. 23, which is much stained and
                                        torn, really belongs to this manuscript, is doubtful. It
                                        contains, on the verso, two short extracts from the writings
                                        of <persName>Severus of
                                            <placeName>Antioch</placeName></persName>. On the recto,
                                        there are three entries of deaths, all of which have been
                                        purposely effaced. The first is that of a bishop. In the
                                        third, the words ܘܡܬܝܢ ܕܛܝܝ̈ܐ are still legible, showing
                                        that these entries belong to the third cent, of the Hijra,
                                            <date>A.D. 815—912</date>.</p>
                                    <p><quote xml:lang="syr"></quote></p>
                                </item>
                            </list>
